{"schema_version":"1.7.3","id":"OESA-2023-1494","published":"2023-08-12T11:05:40Z","modified":"2025-09-03T06:19:20.394520Z","upstream":["CVE-2023-3863","CVE-2023-4132"],"summary":"kernel security update","details":"The Linux Kernel, the operating system core itself.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nA use-after-free flaw was found in nfc_llcp_find_local in net/nfc/llcp_core.c in NFC in the Linux kernel. This flaw allows a local user with special privileges to impact a kernel information leak issue.(CVE-2023-3863)\r\n\r\nA use-after-free vulnerability was found in the siano smsusb module in the Linux kernel. The bug occurs during device initialization when the siano device is plugged in. This flaw allows a local user to crash the system, causing a denial of service condition.(CVE-2023-4132)","affected":[{"package":{"name":"kernel","ecosystem":"openEuler:20.03-LTS-SP1","purl":"pkg:rpm/openEuler/kernel&distro=openEuler-20.03-LTS-SP1"},"ranges":[{"type":"ECOSYSTEM","events":[{"introduced":"0"},{"fixed":"4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe1"}]}],"ecosystem_specific":{"aarch64":["perf-debuginfo-4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe1.aarch64.rpm","python2-perf-debuginfo-4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe1.aarch64.rpm","bpftool-debuginfo-4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe1.aarch64.rpm","python3-perf-debuginfo-4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe1.aarch64.rpm","bpftool-4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe1.aarch64.rpm","python3-perf-4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe1.aarch64.rpm","perf-4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-debuginfo-4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-debugsource-4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-tools-4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-devel-4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-tools-debuginfo-4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe1.aarch64.rpm","python2-perf-4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-tools-devel-4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe1.aarch64.rpm","kernel-source-4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe1.aarch64.rpm"],"src":["kernel-4.19.90-2308.2.0.0213.oe